        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 8:58AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 858 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Cordova, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sayre, Barney, Empire, Rocky Hollow, Sumiton, Burnwell, Beloit,
Quinton, Sipsey, Parrish, Dora, Cordova, Lynns Park, Partridge
Crossroads, West Jefferson, Jasper, Graysville, and Adamsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
